    <div class="container">
        <p class="fs-6 mb-3">
            The core of the programme centred around early access playtesting throughout the development lifecycle of Halo Infinite. This involved hands‑on testing of early builds, providing structured and S.M.A.R.T feedback, and then repeating the process as changes and improvements were introduced. Regular group calls with members of the development team allowed for open discussion, progress updates, and live feedback, creating a strong and continuous feedback loop rather than isolated snapshots of opinion.
        </p>
        <p class="fs-6 mb-3">
            This collaborative approach continued beyond launch, with ongoing playtests, surveys, and discussions helping to refine systems, balance, and player experience over time. Being part of that cycle reinforced how effective feedback works best when it’s timely, clearly structured, and grounded in both player experience and development constraints.
        </p>
        <p class="fs-6 mb-3">
            Alongside this, a key part of the programme was acting as an ambassador for the wider Halo Insider community — helping
            players access test builds, understand what was being tested, and provide useful feedback back to the development team. Bridging that gap between players and developers helped ensure feedback was both accessible and actionable.
        </p>
        <p class="fs-6 mb-3">
            The experience strengthened my understanding of feedback loops, player advocacy, and collaborative iteration — lessons I continue to apply across community moderation, tooling, and engagement. It’s a perspective rooted not just in playing
            games, but in helping shape the spaces and conversations around them.
        </p>
